    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-10-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 11,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 562.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 1151 of the 20th of
                        August last and the copy which you inclose of the last note received from
                        the yamên on the Chi-nan-fu troubles, which, you remark, is simply a
                        repetition of former notes.</p>
                <p>You will, of course, keep the matter in sight and endeavor in all proper ways
                        to further the reasonable desires of Mr. Reid and his associates.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
